# English

This project is osTicket Translator Originally, it was created by "Fullservice Consulting & Services - LLC" through its director and owner which is Analyst and Programmer in various languages, among them PHP.

This project was born from the need to have a simple and functional software for managing calls of our customers. But did not find any software in my native language (Brazilian Portuguese), although there are several, but none reached our expectations.

So I started the translation of the original project osTicket which can be found at: www.osticket.com and is an original work of Peter Rotich <peter@osticket.com>.

Aiming to enable a fruitful result of my work simply so that others also translate and even customize it if osTicket soon, I decided to build a framework following the philosophy of translation for Joomla.

The project became a success and was translated into eight languages, including Portuguese, Spanish, Italian, Dutch, but during the process of version 1.6 of the Original osTicket began to be tested, and how I chose to finish in this weakened version 1.5 , resuming when the WebDesigner Frumau Jasper, translator in Dutch, we decided to distribute it as your own fork called osTicket Reload (by the way a great name), it renegotiated Jasper Frumau my role in the project, even as I had never before GitHub knew well and had 100% capitate his philosophy.

When I realized that the philosophy of GitHub was 100% compatible with my ideas for sharing knowledge, respect for copyright, and exchanging information openly, I found myself in the right place, then also realized that he could resume the translation work on a Fork keeping my own original design, without discarding the effort in Jasper Frumau keep the project alive.

Today the project is already fully adapted to version 1.6 and there are several branchs of action for the development of solutions suggested in the forum osTicket Original and also to merge these new features with the translated version, osTicket Translator.

OsTicket Translator is to interface with the client fully translated, and much of the administration interface and team. Your help is critical to the project.

To participate is very simple to start reading our wiki at: https://github.com/Fullservice/OsTicket/wiki

# Em Português

Este projeto é o OsTicket Translator Original, ele foi criado pela "FullService consultoria e Serviços - Ltda" através de seu diretor e proprietário que é Analista e Programador Pleno em diversas linguagens, dentre elas PHP.

Este projeto nasceu da necessidade de se ter um software simples e funcional para gerenciamento dos chamados de nossos clientes. Porem não encontramos nenhum software no meu idioma de origem (Português Brasileiro), apesar de  existirem vários, mas nenhum atingiu nossa expectativa.

Então iniciei a tradução do projeto Original OsTicket que pode ser encontrado no site: www.osticket.com e é um trabalho original de Peter Rotich <peter@osticket.com>. 

Objetivando permitir que meu trabalho frutificasse um resultado simples para que outros traduzissem também e inclusive personaliza-se o OsTicket mais rapidamente, optei em construir um Framework seguindo a filosofia do Joomla para tradução.

O projeto se tornou um sucesso e foi traduzido para 8 idiomas, dentre eles: Português, Espanhol, Italiano, Holandês, porem durante o processo a versão 1.6  do OsTicket Original começou a ser testada, e como optei em terminar na versão 1.5 este perdeu força, retomando quando o WebDesigner Jasper Frumau, tradutor no Holandês, optou em distribui-lo como seu próprio fork chamado  OsTicket Reload (por sinal um excelente nome), com isto renegociei com Jasper Frumau minha atuação no projeto, até mesmo porque até então eu não conhecia bem o GitHub e não tinha capitado 100% sua filosofia.

Quando percebi que a filosofia do GitHub era 100% compatível com meus ideias de compartilhamento de conhecimento, respeito ao direito autoral, e troca de informação abertamente, vi que estava no lugar certo, então também percebi que poderia retomar o trabalho de tradução em um Fork mantendo minha autoria original no projeto, sem descartar o esforço de Jasper Frumau em manter o projeto vivo.

Hoje o projeto já está totalmente adaptado a versão 1.6 e existem diversos branchs de atuação para desenvolvimento de soluções sugeridas no forum do OsTicket Original e também para merge destes novos recursos com a versão traduzida, OsTicket Translator.

OsTicket Translator está com a interface para o cliente totalmente traduzida, e boa parte da interface de administração e equipe. Sua ajuda é fundamental para o projeto.

Para participar é bem simples inicie lendo nosso wiki no link: https://github.com/FullService/OsTicket/wiki

# Dutch

Dit project is osTicket Translator Oorspronkelijk was het gemaakt door "fullservice Consulting & Services - LLC" door middel van haar directeur en eigenaar, die analist programmeur is in diverse talen, waaronder PHP.

Dit project werd geboren uit de noodzaak om een eenvoudige en functionele software voor het beheren van oproepen van onze klanten hebben. Maar vonden geen software in mijn moedertaal (Braziliaans-Portugees), al zijn er meerdere, maar geen bereikte onze verwachtingen.

Dus begon ik de vertaling van het oorspronkelijke project osTicket die kan worden gevonden op: www.osticket.com en is een origineel werk van Peter Rotich <peter@osticket.com>.

Streven naar een vruchtbare resultaat van mijn werk te kunnen eenvoudigweg zo dat anderen ook vertalen en zelfs aanpassen als osTicket snel, heb ik besloten om een kader op te bouwen na de filosofie van de vertaling voor Joomla.

Het project werd een succes en werd vertaald in acht talen, waaronder het Portugees, Spaans, Italiaans, Nederlands, maar tijdens het proces van versie 1.6 van de Original osTicket begon te worden getest, en hoe ik ervoor gekozen om af in deze verzwakte versie 1.5 , hervatten wanneer de webdesigner Frumau Jasper, vertaler in het Nederlands, hebben we besloten om het te verdelen als je eigen vork genoemd osTicket vernieuwen (door de manier waarop een grote naam), is opnieuw onderhandeld Jasper Frumau mijn rol in het project, zelfs als ik nooit eerder had GitHub goed kende en had 100% capitatum zijn filosofie.

Toen ik me realiseerde dat de filosofie van GitHub was 100% compatibel met mijn ideeën voor het delen van kennis, respect voor het auteursrecht, en uitwisselen van informatie openlijk, vond ik mezelf in de juiste plaats, dan besefte ook dat hij kon het vertaalwerk op een vork resume houden van mijn eigen originele ontwerp, zonder zich ontdoen van de inspanning in Jasper Frumau houden het project in leven.

Vandaag is het project is al volledig aangepast aan versie 1.6 en er zijn verschillende vertakkingen van de actie voor de ontwikkeling van voorgestelde oplossingen in het forum osTicket Original en ook om deze nieuwe functies samen te voegen met de vertaalde versie, osTicket Translator.

OsTicket Translator is om te communiceren met de klant volledig vertaald, en veel van de administratie-interface en het team. Uw hulp is cruciaal voor het project.

deel te nemen aan is heel eenvoudig om te beginnen met het lezen van onze wiki: https: / / github.com / fullservice / osTicket / wiki 
